-- multiSearchAny returns the same rows with and without the index
1	Well, Hello ClickHouse !
2	Well, Hello World !
6	True World Champion
1	Well, Hello ClickHouse !
2	Well, Hello World !
6	True World Champion
Granules: 6/6
Granules: 3/6
-- multiSearchAnyUTF8 behaves identically
1	Well, Hello ClickHouse !
2	Well, Hello World !
6	True World Champion
Granules: 6/6
Granules: 3/6
-- a needle that is absent everywhere prunes all granules
Granules: 6/6
Granules: 0/6
-- the index is recognized by force_data_skipping_indices
3
-- a single word prunes with ngrams (its sub-word grams are indexed), unlike splitByNonAlpha
1	Well, Hello ClickHouse !
2	Well, Hello World !
4	Say Hello !
1	Well, Hello ClickHouse !
2	Well, Hello World !
4	Say Hello !
Granules: 6/6
Granules: 3/6
-- negation stays correct but cannot prune: the index proves a token is present, never that it is absent
3	Good Weather !
4	Say Hello !
5	Its An OLAP Database
3	Good Weather !
4	Say Hello !
5	Its An OLAP Database
-- the "= 0" comparison form negates identically
3	Good Weather !
4	Say Hello !
5	Its An OLAP Database
Granules: 6/6
Granules: 6/6
-- the index is still recognized by force_data_skipping_indices (it is read, just prunes nothing)
3
-- an empty needle array is always false
0
0
